Uses of Interface
javaslang.collection.JStream

  • Packages that use JStream 
    Package Description
    javaslang.collection
    Immutable collections based on JTraversable like the linked list JList and the lazy linked list JStream.
    javaslang.test
    A property check framework built around Property which integrates well with unit test frameworks like junit.

      static class  JStream.AbstractStream<T>
      This class is needed because the interface JStream cannot use default methods to override Object's non-final methods equals, hashCode and toString.
      static class  JStream.Cons<T>
      Non-empty JStream, consisting of a head, a tail and an optional AutoCloseable.
      static class  JStream.Nil<T>
      The empty JStream.
